📦 Installation
1. Clone repo
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/data-sentinel.git
cd data-sentinel
2. Create virtual environment
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate   # Windows
3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
4. Setup environment variables

Create .env file:

OPENAI_API_KEY=your_key_here
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/datasentinel
5. Run backend
uvicorn backend.app.main:app --reload
6. Run frontend
streamlit run frontend/dashboard.py
🐳 Docker (Optional)
docker compose up -d
📡 API Endpoints
Upload CSV
POST /upload-csv
Get reports
GET /reports
Get single report
GET /reports/{id}
AI status
GET /reports/{id}/status
📊 Example Output
{
  "rows": 143,
  "columns": 11,
  "missing_values": {...},
  "column_health": {...},
  "dataset_health_score": 45.45
}
🔐 Design Notes
AI layer is optional and does not block ingestion
All NumPy types are normalized before DB insert
Background tasks handle AI processing asynchronously
System degrades gracefully without OpenAI access
📌 Roadmap
 Advanced drift scoring (KL divergence)
 Real-time streaming ingestion
 Authentication system
 Dataset comparison UI
 Scheduled data quality monitoring
